    b"MemorySearchHints\x00\x00\x01\x00,\x12\x00\x00\x0a        {{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0a\x0a        Choose memory "
    b"search hints for the selected task and current request.\x0a\x0a        The hints will "
    b"drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0a\x0a        Stop once the hints "
    b"look good enough for the request without thinking about it too much.\x0a\x0a        Se"
    b"arch surfaces:\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substring searche"
    b"d.\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each value is ch"
    b"ecked\x0a          as a substring against searchable memory content.\x0a        - stri"
    b"ngs.equals: exact text values. Each value is checked for exact\x0a          equalit"
    b"y against searchable memory content.\x0a\x0a        Optional outputs available in this"
    b" step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be "
    b"useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Return only search hints"
    b" and optional candidate_memory.\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during r"
    b"etrieval; a memory can be useful\x0a          when any positive tag or string hint "
    b"matches.\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0a        - Leave ta"
    b"gs.all_of empty unless compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0a        - Use"
    b" tags.none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0a        - Use strings.contains for dura"
    b"ble words or phrases that should appear\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0a    "
    b"    - Use strings.equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0a      "
    b"    memory value as a whole.\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints o"
    b"ver broad keyword stuffing.\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful search "
    b"hint is available.\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0a\x0a  "
    b"      {{ _.role(\"user\") }}\x0a\x0a        Current user request:\x0a        {{ current_use"
    b"r_request }}\x0a\x0a        Conversation history:\x0a        {% if current_conversation %"
